    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation level. The single deficient factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is accepted under risk-informed rationale: the F1717 protocol is highly standardized, inter-laboratory reproducibility was confirmed across two independent test sites, and the E/uval metric for all QoIs satisfies the pre-specified acceptance threshold. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the Medium assurance level required for this Class II device submission.",
